# Memory system repair

Sequel to [Memory System Review](../memory-system-review/memory-system-review-brief.svx):
the review's eight-item fix list becomes work. Joel chartered it 2026-07-17
("let's grill-master a fix for the wobbly bits") and set scope, authorization,
and the taste bench in one grilling.

## Finish line

- The four mechanical fixes are built, deployed on flagg, and receipted:
  graph privacy boundary (a graph rebuild cannot leak sensitive or excluded
  content — proven by test and by a clean rebuilt `graph.json`), dream cap
  (eligibility is computed over the whole corpus, not the first 200 sorted
  filenames), capture outbox (the 404 route is fixed, the 71 GB backlog is
  safely drained or explicitly dispositioned, and a size/age alarm watches
  the outbox), and release promotion (a receipt-checked script replaces
  manual promotion, with drift detection).
- The taste bench has run: same candidate pool judged with real graded
  history vs stripped history, selection delta published as a receipt —
  the "curator learns" claim gets evidence or gets retracted on the review
  page.
- The five judgment calls are resolved decisions with owners and dates:
  legacy-memory retirement, system-log home, Claude auto-memory, Chorus
  fate, retro writer. Resolved means someone could execute without another
  decision; execution beyond the mechanical four may charter follow-up
  steps here or new efforts.
- The [memory system page](../../resources/memory-system.svx) is updated to
  reflect post-repair reality (regenerated verdicts, not patched sentences,
  per its own maintenance rule).

## Vocabulary

- **wobbly bits** — every item on the review page's fix list, wobbly AND
  gap verdicts alike; Joel's word for the whole batch.
- **mechanical fix** — build work whose shape the review already settled;
  needs receipts, not decisions.
- **judgment call** — a fix that starts with a decision Joel must speak to
  (retirement, ownership, kill-or-keep).
- **safely drained** — outbox backlog is replayed/deduped/dispositioned
  without data loss, double-ingestion, or hammering live services; raw
  deletion only after a step-level check-in.
- **selection delta** — the observable difference in judge picks/scores
  between graded-history and stripped-history runs over identical
  candidates.

## Notes

- Execution authorization (Joel, 2026-07-17): build + deploy on flagg for
  the mechanical fixes; steering reviews, commits, deploys with receipts.
  No public surfaces, no schema migrations, and no deletion of raw data
  without a step-level check-in.
- Skills: `herdr-orchestration` (fan-out), wiki law `joelclaw-wiki/AGENTS.md`
  (privacy is the bar for the graph step), `hunk-review` for diff review.
- The review's four survey assets are the evidence base — workers cite
  them instead of re-surveying:
  [capture-condense](../memory-system-review/capture-condense-survey.svx),
  [brain-stores](../memory-system-review/brain-stores-survey.svx),
  [curation-delivery](../memory-system-review/curation-delivery-survey.svx),
  [periphery](../memory-system-review/periphery-survey.svx).
- Deadline pressure: the dream cap fix wants to land before the corpus
  ages into eligibility (~2026-07-18; nightly dream fires 06:10 local).
- Worker contract deviation (carried from the review effort): workers edit
  only their own step file and named outputs — steering owns this brief.

## Decision ledger

- [Fix the Graph Privacy Boundary](./fix-graph-privacy-boundary.svx) —
  done: shared `isExcludedBrainPage` at build + read-path stripping;
  first safe rebuild 3,082 nodes / 0 sensitive / 0 excluded;
  `graph:build` now part of the normal wiki build (wiki `bc05d5b`).
- [Fix the Dream Cap](./fix-dream-cap.svx) — done: eligibility computed
  over the whole corpus, cap bounds the night's work; reviewed and
  committed (observer `461eddc8`, 87 tests). Release promotion pending
  only on the taste-bench worker's tree clearing.
- [Build the Observer Release Promotion Script](./build-release-promotion-script.svx)
  — done: `bin/promote-release.sh` (clean-tree gate, smoke checks,
  dry-run receipt, log) + release-drift warning in the self-maintenance
  tick; same commit. First real promotion executed 18:14Z: release
  `2e768c2b → 7b5fe928` with receipt — the dream-cap fix is live for the
  06:10 dream.
- [Drain the Capture Outbox](./drain-capture-outbox.svx) — done:
  gateway bounced, two pipeline bugs the drain itself exposed were fixed
  and deployed (empty-run indexing `6877dab1`, step-output size
  `c963c47e`), full drain 167/167 (123 indexed / 44 covered / 0
  failed), alarm live in observer release `01b81cba`. Raw deletion
  pends a check-in.
- The five judgment calls — all resolved in one live grilling (Joel,
  2026-07-17):
  [legacy retirement](./decide-legacy-memory-retirement.svx) — retarget
  `joelclaw recall` to the Brain, archive `memory_observations` to NAS
  then drop it, unregister zombies, delete MEM/FRIC; one PR.
  [Claude auto-memory](./decide-claude-auto-memory.svx) — pointer index:
  migrate facts to Brain `.svx`, MEMORY.md becomes binding rule +
  pointers.
  [Chorus](./decide-chorus-fate.svx) — quiet the canary, park it; Brain
  stays the only substrate.
  [system log](./decide-system-log-home.svx) — retire it (froze 06-22,
  nobody noticed for 25 days); snapshot panda's copy to NAS; OTel +
  observer + Brain already cover the job.
  [retro writer](./decide-retro-writer.svx) — real writer: agent hooks
  send `memory/retro.requested`-style Inngest events with pointers; a
  condenser function writes the retro `.svx`.
  Execution of each is charter-ready follow-up work.
- [Bench Taste Learning](./bench-taste-learning.svx) — done, honest null:
  15 sol:xhigh runs over identical pools (real / nulled / flipped-negative
  history) picked the same memories at the same split. One grade teaches
  nothing measurable. Decisive rerun needs ~20–30 graded sends with both
  polarities; stricter follow-up = near-neighbor candidate pools.
  [Asset](./taste-learning-bench.svx).

## Latent

- Once a few weeks of graded history exist, rerun the taste bench with
  real volume — the first run's delta may be honestly null at one grade.
- If the outbox drain surfaces corrupted or duplicate runs, data repair
  may deserve its own effort.

## Out of scope

- The Chat SDK acting re-flip — owned by
  [messaging-stabilization](../messaging-stabilization/run-shadow-window-cutover.svx)
  with Joel's go already recorded there.
- Brain Graph feature build-out (query surface, cross-root navigation) —
  the [brain-graph](../brain-graph/brain-graph-brief.svx) effort owns it;
  this effort only makes rebuilding SAFE.
- Registering more of the 27 orphan `.brain` trees — the review surfaced
  them; onboarding is per-tree judgment for another day.
